---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';

const siteUrl = (import.meta.env.VITE_SITE_URL || 'https://txcourseguide.com').replace(/\/$/, '');

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'How Texas Defensive Driving Pricing Really Works',
  description: "Texas law sets a $25 minimum for defensive driving — but extra fees can push the real total much higher. Here's exactly what to expect and how to pay the least.",
  url: `${siteUrl}/pricing`,
  datePublished: '2025-01-01',
  dateModified: '2025-01-01',
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'TX Course Guide', url: siteUrl },
  publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'TX Course Guide', url: siteUrl }
};
---

<Layout
  title="How Texas Defensive Driving Pricing Really Works — TX Course Guide"
  description="Texas law sets a $25 minimum for defensive driving — but extra fees can push the real total much higher. Here's exactly what to expect and how to pay the least."
  keywords="Texas defensive driving cost, defensive driving price, TDLR course fee, $25 defensive driving Texas"
  url="/pricing"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <div class="min-h-screen" style="background-color: var(--proto-page-bg); font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;">
    <SiteHeader currentPath="/pricing" />
    <main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[780px] px-4 py-10 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold leading-tight sm:text-3xl" style="color: var(--proto-text);">
        How Texas Defensive Driving Pricing Really Works
      </h1>
      <p class="mb-8 text-[14px]" style="color: var(--proto-text-muted);">
        Published by TX Course Guide · Last updated 2025
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-[15px] leading-relaxed sm:text-[16px]" style="color: var(--proto-text);">
        <p>Searching for the cheapest Texas defensive driving course is a smart move — but "cheapest" can be misleading. Texas state law sets a minimum price that every provider must follow, and most companies layer on additional fees during checkout that can quietly add up well beyond the advertised price.</p>
        <p>This guide breaks down exactly how Texas defensive driving pricing works, what fees to expect, and how to pay as little as legally possible.</p>

        <div class="rounded-lg border px-5 py-4" style="background: var(--proto-teal-bg); border-color: var(--proto-teal-border);">
          <p class="mb-1 text-[13px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: var(--proto-teal-dark);">Quick answer</p>
          <p class="m-0 text-[15px]">The advertised price is almost never the full price. The realistic minimum you should budget is <strong>around $28–$38</strong> depending on whether you need a driving record — even if a course is advertised at $25.</p>
        </div>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-2 mt-10 border-l-4 pl-4 text-lg font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--proto-teal); color: var(--proto-text);">Why Every Texas Defensive Driving Course Costs At Least $25</h2>
          <p>Texas does not let defensive driving providers compete on price below a certain floor. Under rules set by the <strong>Texas Department of Licensing and Regulation (TDLR)</strong>, all approved Driving Safety Course (DSC) providers must charge a minimum of <strong>$25 for the base course</strong>.</p>
          <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 pl-2">
            <li>No legitimate, TDLR-approved course can advertise or sell for less than $25.</li>
            <li>If you see a price under $25, either the company is not properly approved, or the advertised price does not include all required fees.</li>
            <li>Most providers compete right at the floor — $25 — which is why that number appears everywhere.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="my-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-r border-t border-b px-4 py-3" style="border-left-color: #DC2626; background: #FEF2F2; border-color: #FECACA;">
            <p class="mb-1 text-[13px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: #B91C1C;">Watch out</p>
            <p class="m-0 text-[15px]" style="color: var(--proto-text);">A $25 advertised price is the starting point, not the total. Keep reading to see what gets added.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-2 mt-10 border-l-4 pl-4 text-lg font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--proto-teal); color: var(--proto-text);">The Fees That Get Added at Checkout</h2>
          <p>Once you start a course and reach the payment screen, you will often see fees that were not mentioned in the headline price.</p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold" style="color: var(--proto-text);">Processing Fee</h3>
          <p>Almost every provider charges a payment processing fee. This typically runs around <strong>$3</strong>, though some providers charge slightly more or fold it into the base price.</p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold" style="color: var(--proto-text);">Certificate Delivery Fee</h3>
          <p>This is where prices vary the most between providers.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-collapse text-[14px]" style="border: 1px solid var(--proto-card-border);">
              <thead>
                <tr style="background: var(--proto-text); color: #fff;">
                  <th class="px-3 py-2.5 text-left font-semibold">Delivery Method</th>
                  <th class="px-3 py-2.5 text-left font-semibold">Typical Cost</th>
                  <th class="px-3 py-2.5 text-left font-semibold">Notes</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-b" style="border-color: var(--proto-row-border);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Standard mail</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Free or low cost</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Takes several days to arrive. Some providers include this free.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b" style="border-color: var(--proto-row-border); background: var(--proto-hover-bg);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Expedited mail</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Extra fee varies</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Faster delivery.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b" style="border-color: var(--proto-row-border);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Instant download (PDF)</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Often the most expensive option</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Available immediately. Convenient but can cost significantly more.</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-2 mt-10 border-l-4 pl-4 text-lg font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--proto-teal); color: var(--proto-text);">The Texas 3A Driving Record: Don't Overpay for It</h2>
          <p>Many courts require a <strong>Type 3A driving record</strong> from the Texas Department of Public Safety (DPS) as part of the ticket dismissal process.</p>
          <div class="my-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 px-4 py-3" style="border-left-color: var(--proto-teal); background: var(--proto-teal-bg); border-right: 1px solid var(--proto-teal-border); border-top: 1px solid var(--proto-teal-border); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--proto-teal-border);">
            <p class="mb-1 text-[13px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: var(--proto-teal-dark);">Save Money Here</p>
            <p class="m-0 text-[15px]" style="color: var(--proto-text);">
              You can order your Type 3A driving record directly from the Texas DPS at
              <a href="https://www.dps.texas.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold hover:underline" style="color: var(--proto-teal);">dps.texas.gov</a>
              for <strong>$10</strong>. This is almost always cheaper than the add-on price offered by course providers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-2 mt-10 border-l-4 pl-4 text-lg font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--proto-teal); color: var(--proto-text);">What Does the Cheapest Total Really Look Like?</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-collapse text-[14px]" style="border: 1px solid var(--proto-card-border);">
              <thead>
                <tr style="background: var(--proto-text); color: #fff;">
                  <th class="px-3 py-2.5 text-left font-semibold">Item</th>
                  <th class="px-3 py-2.5 text-left font-semibold">Cost</th>
                  <th class="px-3 py-2.5 text-left font-semibold">Notes</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-b" style="border-color: var(--proto-row-border);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Base course price</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">$25.00</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">TDLR-mandated minimum for all providers</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b" style="border-color: var(--proto-row-border); background: var(--proto-hover-bg);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Processing fee</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">~$3.00</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Typical. Varies slightly by provider.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b" style="border-color: var(--proto-row-border);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Certificate (standard mail)</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">$0–$5+</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Some providers include it free; others charge extra</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b" style="border-color: var(--proto-row-border); background: var(--proto-hover-bg);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Type 3A driving record (if required)</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">$10.00</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Order from dps.texas.gov to get the lowest price</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b font-bold" style="background: var(--proto-teal-bg); border-top: 2px solid var(--proto-teal);">
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Realistic minimum total</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">$28–$38+</td>
                  <td class="px-3 py-2.5">Depends on certificate option and whether record is needed</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-2 mt-10 border-l-4 pl-4 text-lg font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--proto-teal); color: var(--proto-text);">How to Pay the Least Amount Possible</h2>
          <ol class="list-inside list-decimal space-y-2 pl-2">
            <li><strong>Choose a provider with a $25 base price</strong> — most do, but confirm before starting.</li>
            <li><strong>Skip optional upgrades</strong> — video, audio, and mobile add-ons are not required.</li>
            <li><strong>Pick standard mail for your certificate</strong> — if your deadline allows it, this is usually the cheapest delivery option.</li>
            <li><strong>Order your Type 3A driving record directly from DPS</strong> at <a href="https://www.dps.texas.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold hover:underline" style="color: var(--proto-teal);">dps.texas.gov</a> for $10.</li>
            <li><strong>Read the full checkout price before entering payment info</strong> — reputable providers show the total before you commit.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <footer class="mt-12 border-t pt-6 text-[13px]" style="border-color: var(--proto-card-border); color: var(--proto-text-muted);">
          <p>This article is for informational purposes only. Fee structures and policies vary by provider and are subject to change. Always verify current pricing directly with your chosen provider. For official TDLR rules, visit <a href="https://www.tdlr.texas.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="font-semibold hover:underline" style="color: var(--proto-teal);">tdlr.texas.gov</a>.</p>
          <p class="mt-2">© 2025 TX Course Guide · txcourseguide.com</p>
        </footer>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-10">
        <a href="/" class="text-[14px] font-semibold hover:underline" style="color: var(--proto-teal);">← Back to guide</a>
      </p>
    </main>
    <SiteFooter />
  </div>
</Layout>
